<br>
We sat at an unoccupied camp in Shadeweaver's Thicket, killing those grey &amp; black alien looking things, forgot the name.  People kept walking into our camp trying to take the mobs, after we broke it.  No conversation, just walk in and sit in camp that we broke.  No response to our conversation attempts.<br>
<br>
They go away a bit after we threaten to train them to death with our monk alt.  [Having to resort to that, and HAVING the monk there to back it up? Wonderful isn't it?]<br>
<br>
After a while, we started seeing nasty OOCs about how WE stole THEIR camp...  This after we've killed like 3 cycles of alien critters, breaking the camp ourselves.  We argue back and forth a bit.<br>
<br>
We watch one of these a-holes grab a mob, and shurg, cause once they get it, it's their mob.  We watch the mob shred the a-hole, and their friends too, and wonder what kind of crack they were smoking.  My friend announces their deaths to the zone, and laughs at them.<br>
<br>
Now we get threats about hacking our ip addresses, and blacklisting on so-and-so guild, etcetera.  We do the usual /report and /petition, which goes onto the usual 4-hour long queue.<br>
<br>
We get the Beastmaster to level 9, try out the pet and spells for a bit, and get bored of it.<br>
<br>
I return to FV, glad to avoid that mindset that pervades much of Tholuxe Paells, and most other blue servers.  :P<br>
<br>
